<task id="012" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6">
  <metadata>
    <title>D-A-11 BIG-BANG MIGRATION (Q9) — Migrate All 10 Pre-R5 Chat Tools to `IToolHandler` + `sprk_analysistool` Rows</title>
    <phase>Phase A — Data-driven Foundation</phase>
    <status>completed</status>
    <estimated-effort>8-12 hours (multi-day — high-risk gate task)</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>011</dependencies>
    <blocks>013</blocks>
    <tags>bff-api, refactoring, ai, chat, migration</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Highest-risk task in Phase A. Modifies/migrates 10 production chat-tool classes; risk to ALL chat-side functionality if rollback path is incomplete. Per project plan risk register R1: "All 10 chat tools migrate in single task → high blast radius." Mandatory comprehensive regression test + documented rollback plan.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Single-task atomic migration per Q9 binding decision. Cannot be split — entire batch lands together with regression gate, or rolls back atomically.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    🚨 HIGH-RISK GATE TASK — Q9 BATCH MIGRATION.

    Migrate all 10 pre-R5 chat tool C# classes to data-driven `IToolHandler` implementations
    + corresponding `sprk_analysistool` Dataverse rows in a SINGLE batch per Q9 binding
    decision. Tools to migrate:

    1. DocumentSearch
    2. AnalysisQuery
    3. KnowledgeRetrieval
    4. TextRefinement
    5. WorkingDocument
    6. AnalysisExecution
    7. WebSearch
    8. CodeInterpreter
    9. LegalResearch
    10. VerifyCitations

    For each tool: (a) extract its logic into an `IToolHandler` implementation
    (`{ToolName}Handler.cs`); (b) seed a `sprk_analysistool` Dataverse row with
    `AvailableInContexts = Chat`, valid `JsonSchema` (task 008) for parameter declaration,
    handler-class binding, description preserved verbatim; (c) verify the existing hardcoded
    class can be deleted (or feature-gated for rollback per ADR-018 / existing flag).

    🔴 CRITICAL ROLLBACK PLAN (mandatory; document in task notes):
    1. Rollback path 1: `git revert` of this PR returns to hardcoded list (task 011's
       fallback path activates with ZERO data-driven rows, restoring hardcoded behavior).
    2. Rollback path 2: Delete all 10 seeded `sprk_analysistool` rows → task 011's
       fallback activates → hardcoded list returns.
    3. Rollback path 3: If both above fail, manually re-enable hardcoded classes via the
       feature flag/gate established in task 011. NO NEW feature flags introduced per
       ADR-018; reuse the existing one.

    🔴 COMPREHENSIVE REGRESSION TEST SUITE (mandatory; gates merge):
    For each of the 10 tools, the regression test MUST exercise every code path:
    - LLM-invoked function call → handler dispatches → result returns correctly
    - Parameter validation (valid JSON, invalid JSON rejected, missing required fields)
    - Error path (handler throws → graceful error response)
    - Authorization path (tenant isolation; cross-tenant invocation blocked)
    - Streaming response (if tool returns streamed content)
    - Telemetry path (ADR-015: tool name + decision + timestamp only; no user message
      content)

    Total minimum test count: 10 tools × 6 paths = 60 regression tests. Migration is NOT
    complete until all 60 pass in staging.

    Critical-path context: this task is the single highest-risk item in Phase A. Task 013
    (regression gate) validates the migration in staging before Phase B can begin. Pillar 3
    (tasks 020-023) cannot start until 013 confirms the batch is functional.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior BFF engineer + AI-platform owner. MUST have prior experience with the 10
    existing chat-tool classes' invocation paths and the chat-agent middleware chain.
    Deep familiarity with NFR-13 safety pipeline + NFR-01 conversational primacy.
  </role>

  <goal>
    All 10 pre-R5 chat tool classes migrated to `IToolHandler` implementations.
    10 `sprk_analysistool` Dataverse rows seeded with `AvailableInContexts = Chat` and
    valid `JsonSchema`. 60+ regression tests pass. Rollback plan documented and tested.
    Build green; publish-size delta reported (net negative expected due to deleted
    hardcoded classes). ADR-015 trace hygiene verified for every migrated tool.
  </goal>

