  <notes>
    <note title="Rollback Plan (binding; MUST be documented in PR + task notes before merge)">
      Three rollback paths in priority order:
      1. `git revert` of this PR. Task 011's fallback path returns hardcoded tool list when ZERO data-driven rows exist.
      2. Delete all 10 seeded `sprk_analysistool` rows via Web API or `pac` script. Task 011 fallback re-activates.
      3. If both above fail in production: re-enable hardcoded classes via existing capability flag established in task 011. NO new feature flags created.

      Rollback drill: BEFORE merging this PR, execute rollback path 2 in staging to confirm the hardcoded fallback re-activates correctly. Record evidence.
    </note>
    <note title="Migration estimate">
      8-12 hours = ~1.5-2 engineer-days. Allocate 1 day to handlers + DI; 0.5-1 day to Dataverse rows + seed script; 0.5 day to regression test authoring; 0.5 day to staging validation + rollback drill.
    </note>
  </notes>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + Rigor Declaration">
      Output: "🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL — Q9 BIG-BANG migration; highest-risk task in Phase A; mandatory regression suite + rollback plan + staging gate". Read R1 risk in plan.md + R5 lessons-learned (`projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/notes/lessons-learned.md`).
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress">
      Verify 011 ✅. Update `current-task.md` to task 012; flag as multi-day high-risk task.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources + Inventory Existing Tools">
      Read inputs + knowledge. Capture baseline publish size. Locate all 10 hardcoded tool classes; for each: capture name, description, parameter contract, current invocation path, telemetry pattern.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Author Rollback Plan Document">
      Create `notes/task-012-rollback-plan.md` with the 3 rollback paths spelled out + staging-validation procedure. Confirm NO new feature flag introduced.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Migrate Tool 1: DocumentSearch">
      Extract logic to `DocumentSearchHandler : IToolHandler`. Author `sprk_analysistool` row JSON (Chat context, JsonSchema, description verbatim). Author regression test covering all 6 paths.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Migrate Tools 2-10 in Sequence">
      Repeat Step 4 for: AnalysisQuery, KnowledgeRetrieval, TextRefinement, WorkingDocument, AnalysisExecution, WebSearch, CodeInterpreter, LegalResearch, VerifyCitations. CHECKPOINT after every 3 tools per CLAUDE.md §5 (Proactive Checkpointing). Build green after each.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Register Handlers in DI">
      Register all 10 new handlers in `AnalysisServicesModule`. Verify no new Program.cs lines.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="🛑 Confirmation Gate — Data Seed Deployment">
      PAUSE per project CLAUDE.md §Confirmation Triggers (10 data-row inserts to production Dataverse entity). Present all 10 row definitions + handler bindings; request approval.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Deploy 10 sprk_analysistool Rows to Dataverse">
      After confirmation: deploy via idempotent seed script using `dataverse-deploy`. Verify all 10 rows; verify `AvailableInContexts = Chat`; verify each row's `JsonSchema` parses cleanly.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Run Regression Suite (60+ tests)">
      Run all regression tests locally. Suite MUST be 100% green. Each tool × 6 paths. Record evidence per tool.
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality Gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `code-review` + `adr-check` against all 10 new handler `.cs` files + DI module + tests. Verify ADR-010/013/014/015/018/027/029 + NFR-01/04/11/13 + FR-12 compliance. Both gates MUST pass.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="🛑 Staging Validation Gate (Q9 mandatory)">
      Deploy to staging. Run regression suite against staging. Execute rollback drill (delete one tool row → confirm fallback to hardcoded → restore). Record evidence. STOP and request human sign-off before merging to master.
    </step>
    <step order="11" name="Delete Hardcoded Tool Classes (after staging validation)">
      Delete the 10 hardcoded tool class files. Run build + regression suite one more time. Confirm green. (If retaining as feature-gated rollback: SKIP this step and document in task notes; per ADR-018 must use existing flag only.)
    </step>
    <step order="12" name="Verify Publish Size">
      `dotnet publish -c Release` → measure delta vs baseline. Net negative size expected (deleted classes). Report absolute + delta in task notes; confirm ≤+5 MB R6 total budget.
    </step>
    <step order="13" name="Document + Complete">
      Update task POML status complete. TASK-INDEX 012 ✅. Reset `current-task.md` to task 013. Report migration summary + rollback plan link + staging-validation evidence + publish-size delta. Notify human reviewer that Q9 batch landed.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">build, test, publish</tool>
    <tool name="pac">Dataverse seed deployment + verification</tool>
    <tool name="dataverse-deploy">Skill for solution / data deployment</tool>
    <tool name="mcp__dataverse__create_record">MCP — seed `sprk_analysistool` rows</tool>
    <tool name="mcp__dataverse__read_query">MCP — verify rows after seed</tool>
    <tool name="git">stage + commit + manage rollback via `git revert`</tool>
    <tool name="code-review">Quality gate Step 9.5</tool>
    <tool name="adr-check">ADR compliance gate Step 9.5</tool>
  </tools>

